&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The script serves as a Proof of Concept (PoC) to exploit a command injection vulnerability in a web application.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It demonstrates how an attacker can execute arbitrary commands on the target system through the vulnerability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;By injecting specially crafted commands, the attacker gains unauthorized access to the system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This unauthorized access can lead to further exploitation, such as data theft, system compromise, or launching other attacks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s crucial to emphasize that exploiting vulnerabilities without proper authorization is both illegal and unethical.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="medium-level"&gt;Medium Level
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Functionality Check&lt;/strong&gt;: Application continues to execute OS commands.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Validation&lt;/strong&gt;: Concatenated &lt;code&gt;|&lt;/code&gt; as payload.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bypass&lt;/strong&gt;: Used &lt;code&gt;|ls -la&lt;/code&gt; payload for successful execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
